mmary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Slot A: \"manual summary composition\" plus requirement for \"auditable warning record.\" Slot B: API/command input ↔ policy check ↔ audit-log persistence boundary. Slot C: Unit validation of flag parsing misses missing/failed audit-record write across modules. Higher levels rejected: no behavior text requires real OS/network/subprocess or real model output.","test_description":"Exercise override endpoint/service with and without explicit override flag using local persistence: without flag, override attempt is rejected; with flag, operation succeeds and an audit warning record is persisted with actor, round, and reason metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Slot A: \"without rerunning review agents after fixes\" and requirement that round id is \"produced after the latest fix commit.\" Slot B: commit-metadata source ↔ review-round metadata ↔ gate finalization check boundary. Slot C: Unit timestamp/hash comparison can pass while real module wiring associates wrong round/commit. Higher levels rejected: behavior text does not require real git subprocess/network; it requires consistency of stored metadata relationships.","test_description":"Create local records for fix commits and review rounds; attempt PASS finalization with (a) stale round id before latest fix commit and (b) fresh round id after latest fix commit; assert only (b) is accepted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Slot A: \"live review loop\" and \"fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.\" Slot B: gate correctness depends on real LLM-stage execution artifact for the updated diff (run actually occurred in live loop). Slot C: Integration with stubbed agent-run completion can falsely pass even when real agent invocation/update-diff handoff is broken. Rejected Workflow: behavior requires one fresh agentic round before finalization, not multiple required agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run end-to-end review loop with real review-agent call on an updated diff: verify PASS finalization is blocked before fresh run completion and allowed only after a new round id from that live run is recorded for the updated diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Slot A: \"rounds are exhausted\" with unresolved \"MUST-FIX findings in stored results.\" Slot B: policy engine ↔ stored findings/round-counter state boundary. Slot C: Unit on escalation rule alone misses state handoff bugs between round tracking and findings repository. Higher levels rejected: behavior is explicitly about stored results and policy outcome, not real OS or model-output quality.","test_description":"Seed local store with max-rounds-reached state and unresolved MUST-FIX findings; execute final outcome computation via service layer; assert outcome is escalation and PASS is impossible.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.02,